reviews.review_text:
Very Nice Topnotch sound and recording. Pretty good performance.

All songs are well-played and well-sung. Solid representation of that era.

4.5 stars
11-14-87 I agree with Evan S. Hunt.

87 FUN Great piece of work from the comeback year...Enjoy the Energy of a really Kind Listen Folks :o) Phils is obviously is good form outta the gates....Bass lines dancin' on air....have a blast kids !!
Very fine post-coma Dead Very good show from the period just after Jerry's coma recovery.  1987 was a good year.
Awesome Job, Great Show! DSO just did this concert 2 nights ago in Indianapolis--such a great setlist, had to give the original a listen...fantastic

Maggie's Farm-Cumberland Blues This combo was played very few times and this one really stands out for me. Bob doesn't sing much of the first verse, but karaoke that part, After that, Jerry hits familiar ground that sounds to me like Winterland Arena, 10-18-76 show during China Cat, check me if I'm wrong. Last verse you really hear Jerry's midwest twang when he sings: Everybody wants me to be just like them. Cumberland Blues is almost as good as Alpine but the highlight for me is Jerry's vocals on Lot a poor men got the Cumberland Blues, he can't win for losing. I was at this show, 20th row on the floor and remember these songs like it happened yesterday.

Til my tale is told and done If Evan S Hunt gives it 5 stars 
then take it to the bank it is 5 stars
and I believe the key is to rate this based 
on 1987 besides being not only post coma
but also being a summer of Dylan./Dead shows
This show is fired up from start to finish.
Hey Pocky Way mid set seems like a rarity?.

19 years old I was.. The Queen Mary parked in dock close by.
This was my second show ever
and I really hit an epic one
by the grace of the stars.
I will NEVER forget.
Matt and Scott were with me..
Thank goodness for all of this.
